Frankfurt am Main (AFP) – Germany’s competition watchdog said on Tuesday that Facebook was abusing its dominant position to “limitlessly” harvest user data from outside websites and apps, allowing its advertisers to target customers with hyper-specific ads.

In a preliminary assessment, the Federal Cartel Office (FCO) said it had focused its probe on the US social media giant’s use of third-party sites to track users’ browsing behaviour
